/// Author
@node AUTHOR "Author"

@{b}About the author of AmID3@{ub}

Hi!

As you might have noticed I'm Fredrik Rambris. A 21-year old guy. I've graduated from school and now works at a local computerstore where I are fixing PCs problems (believe me... the problems are many).

At sparetime I use my beloved Amiga 1200T (no Zorro-board) for Net-sufing and programming. The C-programming I learnt in school from a very talented teacher named Bertil Levau (HEJ!) and it was he who actually got me understanding the C language. Ofcause we worked with PCs and Borland Turbo C but with some help of the Autodocs, the RKRMs and a LOT of help from the guys at #AmigaSWE (Hej Blast, inm8, DANA!!! o ni andra) I finally got into the Amiga system (sometimes a hell but very dynamic!).

Other nice little programs I've made (not counting the thousands in AMOS from my pre c-time):

· @{b}YAMPW@{ub} - Encrypts a string to that of the password in the YAM config. Allowed me to change the password from the outside.

· @{b}Kaka@{ub} - A program which randomly prints out a quote from a file. Made totally in strict ANSI C and very portable. Inspired from IntuiCookie (but no GUI).

· @{b}Amiga Internet-Kit@{ub} - A collection of internet-software bundled with a super easy-to-use installer totallt in swedish. Also features premade settings for the morepart of the swedish ISPs.

· @{b}YAPY@{ub} - An integration of PGP into YAM. (comm/mail/yapy.lha) YAM 2.0 however makes this obsolete by having built-in PGP-support.

