///


/// Usage

@node USAGE "Usage"

AmID3 is a CLI-tool, meaning that you operate it by typing rather than clicking.

The syntax is as follows:

AmID3 <FILENAME> [MODE] [PARAMETERS]

@{b}FILENAME@{ub}
Path to the file to work with. Ex. MP3:NiceOne.mp3

@{b}MODES@{ub}
After the filename you select what to do. There are currently 7 modes to choose from. 

@{b}READ (R)@{ub} - Reads the contents of the ID3 tag if present. This one is default

@{b}SHORT (S)@{ub} - Much like READ. However this one only shows a compact output. [Artist] - [Songname]. Useful for renaming, bbs-dizes and such.

@{b}WRITE (W)@{ub} - Writes/alters conetent of the ID3 tag. If noone is present one will be created. Only the fields entered will be altered. You may use the following fields:
@{b}SONGNAME@{ub}  - Name of the song (30 chars)
@{b}ARTIST@{ub}    - Artist's name (30 chars)
@{b}ALBUM@{ub}     - From wich album it came from (30 chars)
@{b}YEAR@{ub}      - Year of creation (4 chars)
@{b}COMMENT@{ub}   - Just a comment (30/28 chars)
@{b}GENRE@{ub}     - Genre of song (number: 0-114, 255)
@{b}SONGNUM@{ub}   - Which track it was on CD/LP. (number: 1-255)
 Note: This field is stored in the end of the comment field. If you choose to use this field the comment can only hold 28 chars.

For a list of genres you supply the mode @{b}LISTGENRES@{ub} like this:
AmID3 LISTGENRES

@{b}DELETE (D)@{ub} - Erases the ID3-tag if any. This is done by shortening the file by 128-bytes (the size of an ID3-tag).

@{b}EXTRACT (X)@{ub} - Extracts just the ID3-tag outputs it to a separate file.
Ex. AmID3 "S.P.O.C.K-I Am An Android.mp3" X Ram:android.tag
This will copy the ID3-tag from "S.P.O.C.K-I Am An Android.mp3" and write it to a new file called Ram:android.tag. If the file already exists it will be overwritten. Be careful.

@{b}IMPORT (I)@{ub} - Imports an ID3-tag from another file (MP3-file or just a tag-file)
Ex. AmID3 "S.P.O.C.K-I Am An Android.mp3" I "S.P.O.C.K-In Space Noone Can Hear You Scream.mp3"
or AmID3 "S.P.O.C.K-I Am An Android.mp3" I Ram:android.tag
Will read the tag from the file given and write it to "S.P.O.C.K-I Am An Android.mp3"


You may also give some all-time parameters:
If you want to stop AmID3 to barf out status-messages, logos etc you may use the @{b}QUIET@{ub} switch. If you just want to hide the banner you can use the @{b}NOBANNER@{ub}.


Workbench usage:

Set AmID3 as Default Tool in the projecticon of an MP3 file
or
Select AmID3, hold Shift while double-clicking on an MP3 file.

@endnode

///


/// Translations

@node TRANSLATIONS "Translations"

AmID3 is localised, meaning that if you have Workbench 2.1 or later AmID3 will communicate in your language if possible.

Now to make this possible I need your help. If your language isn't in the catalogs-dir of this archive then load the @{b}AmID3.ct@{ub} into a normal texteditor (like C:Ed) and translate the strings.

Heres the top of AmID3.ct:

## version $VER: AmID3.catalog 1.0 ([day].[month].[year])
## codeset 0
## language [please fill in]
;
MSG_OK

; OK
;
MSG_REQUEST

; AmID3 Request
;


Fill in day, month and year at the top and your language in [please fill in]. Ex. Svenska, Deutch etc.
On the empty lines fill in the translations... Like this:

## version $VER: AmID3.catalog 1.0 (@{b}16@{ub}.@{b}5@{ub}.@{b}98@{ub})
## codeset 0
## language @{b}svenska@{ub}
;
MSG_OK
@{b}OK@{ub}
; OK
;
MSG_REQUEST
@{b}AmID3 Förfrĺgan@{ub}
; AmID3 Request
;


Save your changes and mail the file to me and I'll include it in the next release of AmID3 along with your name in this guide.


List of translators:
Svenska - Fredrik Rambris <fredrik.rambris@amiga.nu> (me)
Espańol - Jesús Reyes Martinez <jreyes@idecnet.com>
Polski - Tomasz Kepa <domel@box43.gnet.pl>

@endnode

///


/// History

@node History "History"

 v1.5 (98-05-23)
   · Polish catalog added. Translated by Tomasz Kepa <domel@box43.gnet.pl>
   · Made the sourcecode run through SAS/C w/o warnings or errors. All versions of AmID3 have been made with StormC. I've ordered SAS/C wich will result in future AmID3 will be made in SAS/C instead. This means that it's easier to code MUI stuff etc and a GUI WILL be made.
   · Fixed a bug. The catalog wasn't closed after usage.

 v1.4 (98-05-16)
   · The line that separates the banner from the output in READ now is gone when NOBANNER is set.
   · Spannish catalog added. Translated by Jesús Reyes Martinez <jreyes@idecnet.com>.
   · READ is now default and can therefor be omitted. Ex. AmID3 FunnyTune.mp3.
   · Revised this guide a bit. Especially the @{"Usage" link USAGE}-section

 v1.3 (98-05-01)
   · Added option NOBANNER. Disables the AmID3-banner shown before anything else. Useful for batch-scripts etc.
   · Added option SHORT. Outputs just artist and songname (if set) like this [Artist] - [Songname]. Useful for renaming-scripts etc.  [Hej Zynx!!]
   · AmID3 now gives returncodes to the CLI it was run from. 5 for the most errors and 10 if it can't allocate memory.

 v1.2 (98-04-25) - Revisions are adding fast.
   · Added option EXTRACT. Extracts the ID3-tag (128 bytes) to a named separate file. 
   · Added option IMPORT. Imports the ID3-tag from a named separate file. 
   · When adding parameters all the time they got mixed up and the results was quiet goofy. Now fixed.
   · AmID3 is now localised and if you make translations to your own language please send the CT-file to me. Address in @{"Author" link AUTHOR}.

 v1.1 (98-04-24)
   · Added option DELETE. Deletes the ID3-tag if any from file.
   · Fixed a bug which made the text "No ID3-tag" only to lie in memory and not showing it.
   · Fixed a spelling error in the manual.

 v1.0 (98-04-19)
   · Initial Aminet-release.
   · Got the idea and coded it over a night.

@endnode

